<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301941">Figure 41</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301941" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301941" filename="../figg13/G1301941.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the auxiliary housing in a vise. Remove the auxiliary countershaft retaining straps
                or rear bearing covers, shim and rear bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301942">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301942" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301942" filename="../figg13/G1301942.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Remove Rear Bearing Covers, Shim and Rear Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The countershaft will fall loose in the auxiliary section.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to partially drive the output shaft forward (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301943">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301943" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301943" filename="../figg13/G1301943.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Drive Output Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary countershafts from the auxiliary section case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301944">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301944" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301944" filename="../figg13/G1301944.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Remove Auxiliary Countershafts From Auxiliary Section Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, secure the countershaft assemblies in a vise and remove both the front and
                rear bearings with a bearing separator and jaw pullers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301945">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301945" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301945" filename="../figg13/G1301945.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Remove Front and Rear Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
